Food

As discussed above, despite low income among North Korean citizens, food accounted for 46.8% of total household spend, according to North Korean government.

Recent reports from the Ethiopian Poultry Association of Asia-Pacific region show that the North Korean market, in comparison with other African markets, is such an underexplored market, having 50% of the GDP per capita lower than that of Somalia. Less companies seem to be investing in the North Korean market, as North Korea resides in such a niche position, with an illiteracy rate of 27% and the lowest urbanisation rate in the world.
